parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of control, leading to accidents, and can also leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: often at slow to idle speeds

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate speedometer readings can lead to unsafe driving, as drivers may not be aware of their actual speed.
symptoms: Speedometer displaying incorrect or erratic readings
sometimes stuck at a specific speed or fluctuating wildly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical issues can cause a range of problems, including stalling, loss of power, and failure of critical systems.
symptoms: and failure of systems such as the speedometer

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the instrument cluster can lead to a loss of critical information, such as speed, fuel level, and engine performance.
Brake system malfunctions can lead to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: including failure of the anti-lock braking system (ABS) and traction control system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition system failure can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: including failure of the ignition relay and spark plugs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine damage, overheating, and stalling.
The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Loud whining or moaning noise when turning the wheel
binding or sticking of the steering wheel
and vibrations felt in the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Loud knocking sound when moving the steering wheel
vibrations felt in the steering wheel

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Loud clicking sound when turning the wheel
and vibrations felt in the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of steering control can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
The engine stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine suddenly shuts off without warning
often while driving at various speeds
including highway speeds; the vehicle may stall while decelerating or accelerating; the engine may restart easily

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating engine can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle overheats while driving at various speeds; the temperature gauge rises rapidly; the vehicle may shut down or stall; the coolant temperature sensor may malfunction; the thermostat may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uncontrollable acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: even when the driver takes their foot off the gas pedal; the brakes may not respond as expected; the vehicle may continue to accelerate despite attempts to slow down.
